{"title_page": "Sanctissimus Dominus Noster", "text_new": "{{italic title}}\n{{unreferenced|date=September 2010}}\n'''''Sanctissimus Dominus Noster''''' is a [[papal bull]] of [[Pope Urban VIII]] which was given on 13 March 1625.\n\n==Purpose==\n\nThe document's main purpose was to regulate the Catholic faithful against giving devotion to deceased persons reputed to have died in holiness without the consent of the [[Apostolic See]]. The bull was also a foundational document in the history of the Catholic Church's process of [[beatification]] and [[canonization]].\n\n==Highlights of the document==\n\nIn ''Sanctissimus Dominus Noster'', Catholic faithful are told not to have images of deceased persons reputed to have died in holiness with halos, laurels and rays around their head.  The bull also states that no one can print anything on alleged [[private revelation]]s without the consent of the local Bishop or the [[Apostolic See]].  Any violations of the bull would incur punishment.\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Iconography]]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:17th-century papal bulls]]\n[[Category:Revelation]]\n[[Category:1625 works]]\n[[Category:Documents of Pope Urban VIII]]\n[[Category:1625 in Christianity]]\n\n\n{{RC-Canon-law-stub}}\n{{RC-document-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{italic title}}\n{{unreferenced|date=September 2010}}\n'''''Sanctissimus Dominus Noster''''' is a [[papal bull]] of [[Pope Urban VIII]] which was given on 13 March 1625.\n\n==Purpose==\n\nThe document's main purpose was to regulate the Catholic faithful against giving devotion to deceased persons reputed to have died in holiness without the consent of the [[Apostolic See]]. The bull was also a foundational document in the history of the Catholic Church's process of [[beatification]] and [[canonization]].\n\n==Highlights of the document==\n\nIn ''Sanctissimus Dominus Noster'', Catholic faithful are told not to have images of deceased persons reputed to have died in holiness with halos, laurels and rays around their head.  The bull also states that no one can print anything on alleged [[private revelation]]s without the consent of the local Bishop or the [[Apostolic See]].  Any violations of the bull would incur punishment.\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2010}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Iconography]]\n\n[[Category:17th-century papal bulls]]\n[[Category:Revelation]]\n[[Category:1625 works]]\n[[Category:Documents of Pope Urban VIII]]\n[[Category:1625 in Christianity]]\n\n\n{{RC-Canon-law-stub}}\n{{RC-document-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rich Farmbrough", "label": "safe", "comment": "Update date format tag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sanctissimus_Dominus_Noster"}
